  "prompt": "What is the best way to get change for the new 2000 INR note?",
  "response": "Getting change for the new 2000 INR note can be tricky due to its high denomination. Here are the best approaches, along with some considerations:\n\n**Best Strategies:**\n\n*   **Large Retailers/Supermarkets:** These places generally have a higher cash flow and are more likely to be able to break a 2000 note. Try larger chains like Reliance Retail, DMart, or Big Bazaar.\n*   **Petrol Pumps:** While some might be hesitant, petrol pumps usually handle significant amounts of cash and *should* be able to provide change, *especially if you are buying fuel*.\n*   **Banks:** Your bank is the most reliable option.  Go during off-peak hours to avoid long queues.\n*   **ATMs (Sometimes):** Some ATMs allow you to deposit cash. Deposit the 2000 note and then withdraw smaller denominations. Check if your bank's ATMs offer this facility. This can sometimes be a way to get change without needing to interact with a teller.\n\n**Secondary Strategies (May Be Less Reliable):**\n\n*   **Restaurants:** If you're dining out, especially at a larger restaurant, they may be able to accommodate your request.\n*   **Movie Theaters:** Similar to restaurants, movie theaters often handle large cash transactions.\n*   **Pharmacies:** Larger pharmacies, especially those open 24 hours, may have enough change.\n*   **Ask Friends/Family/Colleagues:**  The simplest solution might be to ask someone you know if they can make change for you.\n\n**Tips for Success:**\n\n*   **Be polite and patient:** Explain your situation politely. Avoid demanding change, as businesses are not obligated to provide it.\n*   **Consider making a small purchase:**  Buy a small item to make it easier for the establishment to provide change.\n*   **Go during business hours:** Avoid trying to get change late at night when businesses may have less cash on hand.\n*   **Spread your attempts:** Don't try to break the entire stack of 2000 notes at one location.\n*   **Don't go during peak hours:** Shops will be less willing to assist during busy times.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Legality:**  Refusing to accept legal tender is generally not permitted, but there's no obligation for a vendor to provide change if they don't have it.\n*   **Authenticity:** Be prepared to prove that the note is genuine if asked.\n*   **UPI and Digital Payments:**  The best and most convenient option these days is to use UPI, credit/debit cards, or other digital payment methods whenever possible to avoid the need for change.\n\n**In summary, a bank is your best bet.  Large retailers and petrol pumps are usually reliable. Be polite, and consider making a small purchase to make it easier for businesses to help you.**\n",
